bib_record.title: Measurement of gamma-ray spectra accompanying radiative capture of nucleons

free_txt: Full information
Partial and total capture cross sections in tables
Experimental setup. Full paper.
NaI(Tl) crystal placed in a lead cylinder
enclosed in a paraffin layer containing boron carbide.
On the target side, only paraffin with lithium hydride
was used.
0.8 Ci T absorbed by Ag (15 um) and Ti
(0.45 mg/cm2) on Cu backing.
The small distance of the sample from the tritium
target (3 mm) was the cause of considerable neutron
energy spreads.
Direct detection of gammas. The 'immediate' background
is reduced by the shielding system of the crystal
whereas the 'delayed' background is lowered owing to
the pulsed proton beam.
Absolute measurement
Experimental setup
Identical to P,INDC(POL)-3,26,1970
Theoretical calculation of capture cross sections
18 mm diam., 12 mm thick, shielded against thermal
neutrons by a Cd foil (0.5 mm thick)
